2007-05-04  David Cantrell  <dcantrell@redhat.com>

	* loader2/linuxrc.s390: Sanity check network information so we get
	correct data written to the ifcfg-ethX scripts (#234152).

	* loader2/loader.c (doLoaderMain): Remember early network bring-up
	so we don't try to bring networking up in stage 2 if we already have
	it. Prompt for information when DHCP fails (#232400).
	* loader2/net.c (kickstartNetworkUp): Likewise.

	* isys/isys.py (umount): Don't traceback when trying to remove the
	/mnt/sysimage tree because we may have /var/lib/rpm data in there
	already. Occurs when users start a new install and then decide to
	cancel it and proceed with an upgrade (#227650).

	* network.py: Write correct info to /etc/sysconfig/network (#222147).

